{"id":34961,"date":"2021-01-17T15:49:54","date_gmt":"2021-01-17T11:49:54","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=34961"},"modified":"2021-01-17T23:01:32","modified_gmt":"2021-01-17T19:01:32","slug":"ibrahim-khuluq-jannah","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/01\/17\/ibrahim-khuluq-jannah\/","title":{"rendered":"Ibrahim on Character: Asking Allah to give Paradise to the wrongdoer"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Al-Qushayri reported: Ibrahim ibn Adham, may Allah have mercy on him, went out to one of the prairies and he was confronted by a soldier. The soldier said, \u201cWhere are the residents?\u201d Ibrahim pointed to the graveyard, so the soldier struck his head and wounded him. When the soldier passed by later, it was said to him, \u201cHe is Ibrahim ibn Adham, the ascetic of Khorasan!\u201d The soldier came to him apologizing, and Ibrahim said, \u201cWhen you struck me, I asked Allah Almighty to give you Paradise.\u201d The soldier said, \u201cWhy?\u201d Ibrahim said, \u201cI knew I would be rewarded for it, so I did not want my share from you to be good and your share from me to be evil.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Risa\u0304lah al-Qushayri\u0304yah 2\/401<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right\">\u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0642\u0634\u064a\u0631\u064a \u0623\u064e\u0646 \u0625\u0650\u0628\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0627\u0647\u0650\u064a\u0645 \u0628\u0652\u0646 \u0623\u062f\u0647\u0645 \u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u062e\u0631\u062c \u0625\u0650\u0644\u064e\u0649 \u0628\u064e\u0639\u0652\u0636 \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631\u0627\u0631\u064a \u0641\u0627\u0633\u062a\u0642\u0628\u0644\u0647 \u062c\u0646\u062f\u064a \u0641\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0623\u064a\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0645\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0641\u0623\u0634\u0627\u0631 \u0625\u0650\u0644\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0642\u0628\u0631\u0629 \u0641\u0636\u0631\u0628 \u0631\u0623\u0633\u0647 \u